longBusinessSummary: HEC Infra Projects Limited operates as an engineering, procurement, and construction (EPC) contractor for electro-mechanical and instrumentation projects in India. The company offers services for transmission and substation projects, water management systems, smart lighting systems, public address systems, solar rooftops and power plants, building management systems, and air conditioning systems, as well as fire, security, and nurse calling systems; and engineering consulting services. It also provides services for industrial and commercial electrification; battery energy storage systems; mini/micro grid solar projects; extra low voltage systems; switchyards, overhead transmission lines, and underground cable laying; extra-high voltage cable and communication backbone networks; computer networking, fire alarm systems, door access control, and CCTV control; water pumping stations; and EPC and installation of indoor and outdoor lighting, as well as solar, smart street, industrial plant, river front, and highway lighting solutions; and high transmission and low transmission panels, and distribution boards. The company serves the engineering and allied industries; textile, glass, and cement industries; chemical, pharmaceutical, and food products; steel and non-ferrous industries; petrochemical, refineries, and gas and oil sectors; commercial projects; dairy and allied industries; paint industry; airports; hotels; industrial and power-generation plants; hospitals; ports; commercial centers; banks; malls; multiplexes; call centers; and software parks and SEZs. HEC Infra Projects Limited was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Ahmedabad, India.
